snippet.textDisplay: To the people who take the video clip as a simple horror zompie cliche, the entire song and video is inspired by the stoic philosophy. The name itself memento mori, means the  inevitability of death,not as something to be terrified of but something to makes us liberated from the prison of everyday routine. Now matter how grave something in our lives feels, it will be meaningless in the end as we are all going to die anyway. The difference of stoicism with nihilism is that in stoicism  the knowledge of death must be used to better yourself. You are temporary, your loved ones are too. So do the best you can do as human being and love as much as you can because you are not gonna be here for long. The songs tries to depict this in my opinion. The dude is hunted by his everyday fears(zombies) that aren't trully there  and can't escape them no matter what. He needs to "wake up" and come to realisation that he is wasting his life running way from his fears.

snippet.textDisplay: People should better be asking why the song was written before the official outbreak. Can't wait for the album. Lamb of God still have one of the best flow in metal, perhaps even in general, I dare you to sit still while listening; and great overall production,amazing sound. Btw.talking pandemic, anyone weirded out by the Netflix series "Pandemic" which came out few days before the news of the outbreak. So many little indicators in hindsight, but Bill Gates is the memento mori, without a doubt.
